"Sing to Yahweh a new song, Sing to Yahweh all the earth."
"Sing to Yahweh, bless His name, Proclaim from day to day His salvation."
"Declare among nations His honour, Among all the peoples His wonders."
"For great  Yahweh, and praised greatly, Fearful He  over all gods."
"For all the gods of the peoples `are' nought, And Yahweh made the heavens."
"Honour and majesty `are' before Him, Strength and beauty in His sanctuary."
"Ascribe to Yahweh, O families of the peoples, Ascribe to Yahweh honour and strength."
"Ascribe to Yahweh the honour of His name, Lift up a present and come in to His courts."
"Bow yourselves to Yahweh, In the honour of holiness, Be afraid of His presence, all the earth."
"Say among nations, `Yahweh hath reigned, Also -- established is the world, unmoved, He judgeth the peoples in uprightness.'"
"The heavens joy, and the earth is joyful, The sea and its fulness roar."
"The field exulteth, and all that  in it, Then sing do all trees of the forest,"
"Before Yahweh, for He hath come, For He hath come to judge the earth. He judgeth the world in righteousness, And the peoples in His faithfulness!"
